<TITLE> AL to end mourning with condolence meeting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 13 (bdnews24.com)The Awami League concludes on Wednesday its three-day mourning programme over the death of prime minister Sheikh Hasina's husband Dr MA Wazed Miah through a citizen condolence meeting. The meeting would be held at Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre at around 4pm with the cabinet members, politicians, scientists and educationists highlighting his life and work. The ruling party hoisted black flag and kept the party flag at half-mast in the party offices across the country during its three-day programme that began on Monday. It also held doa and milad mahfil at the party headquarters and prayer sessions in the mosques, temples and churches. The central working committee at a meeting on Sunday announced the mourning programme to pay tribute to Dr Miah, a nuclear scientist, who died on Saturday. Dr Miah was buried at his family graveyard in his village home at Pirganj, Rangpur on Sunday. His qulkhwani will be held on Thursday at the prime minister's official residence Jamuna
